snippet.textDisplay: I am going to try and keep this 100. I agree that Charlo won the 1st fight because he outboxed Harrison 9/12 rounds, landed more shots, landed harder shots, and, importantly, he was the champion going into that first fight with the title. Not to knock Harrison, but he did fight well as he was better defensively, more accurate, landed the cleaner shots, and overall, just the more "crispier" fighter. He used his jab for good, clean offensive strikes and great body work and footwork for defense. However, I did not believe he should have been declared the victor because he simply did not do enough to win. He really only controlled the fight for about 4-5 rounds at max with his jab, but that simply is not enough in my book to win especially when facing the champion. No one was dropped and Charlo rattled Harrison on multiple occasions and kept Harrison at bay with his power punches. Also, since Charlo was outlanding Harrison on a more consistent basis, he outworked Harrison and if anything, the fight should have been a victory for Charlo or a longshot draw.As for this 2nd fight, I definitely had Harrison winning the fight despite the knockdown. I had him up by 3 rounds. Harrison did much better this fight. I was impressed with his performance. The defense was even more superb as this time, he was blocking punches along with weaving out of the way of the hits. His accuracy did not surprise me as he did that the first fight. He made the mistake going toe to toe with Charlo and failed to respect his power and it cost him the fight when that hook landed in the 11th round. Ever since the knockdown, he seemed to recover, but when was dropped the 2nd time in the 11th round, that looked bad and I could have seen the referee stopping the fight. Although he got back up, Harrison appeared to be getting harassed by the barrage of punches Charlo threw to seal the deal. It may have looked like an early stoppage, but when a person is not engaging after multiple knockdowns, a referee stepping is not always a bad stoppage. I felt it was a reasonable stoppage considering Harrison not fighting back. Charlo will need to improve on his accuracy as that is his biggest flaw. The boy's got a chin, but against a powerful puncher, that could be costly if he is caught. Still, great win for him.
